            <p>The relationship in the Torah between tzara'as (a skin disease induced by spiritual impurity) and the sin of loshon hora is well known. Moshe's righteous sister Miriam was afflicted with tzara'as because she said something about Moshe that had just the slightest taint of loshon hora. Her words were well intentioned and she spoke only to her brother Aaron, yet she was immediately punished with tzara'as and the Jewish people had to delay travel for seven days until she was cured.</p>

